node.text: @heatherjmarks 💯
If that is your baby girl, then my God, she is so cute, I watched the video at least 10 times, because 💙💙💙 My heart melted :)

Of course many will say “Lucky you!  At least you don’t have to co-parent with a narcissist.”
.
.
.
And I’m sure people who make such comments aren’t meaning to be invalidating.  But there actually is an element of invalidation in such comments.  Which is why I’d like to acknowledge all the women out there who’ve been abused and left pregnant  by narcissists and sociopaths who’ve refused to even acknowledge their own children. 
Yes, it’s true that a #sociopath or #narcissist is incapable of being a healthy parent.
However, here’s the thing......To carry and give birth to and nurture a child that has been thoroughly disrespected, ignored and spoken about with contempt by the very “man” who created the baby is a kind of trauma you cannot even fathom unless you’ve been through it.
.
.
.
#motherhood #love #family #overcomingtrauma #abusedwhilepregnant #metoo #singlemamas #deadbeatdad #newlife #narcissisticabuse #sociopathawareness #proudaunty #narcissisticpersonalitydisorder
@farmerbillz same here
@ogrebellove13 they said they can’t be a good parent
@farmerbillz a “good dad” doesn’t abuse a Mom. Partner abuse is legally considered child abuse in some places.
What if they are good dad, but mean to me

@healingfromnarcissisticabuse thank you.
I believe one of the most powerful things we can do for ourselves and our children is to speak our truth and speak up 💗
@lifeafternarc I agree, the truth holds up a mirror to an abuser and they hate what they see reflected back to them xx

I admire your bravery, you have to be a mother and father to your beautiful baby but you can do it, you will be a better father than that a******e who abused you ever could be. You're inspirational xx
Congrats to your brother. What do you use to create your text posts like that?
@heather_marie_76 yup, they literally don’t give a shit about their own child. That’s as low as it gets.

While I sat alone waiting for pregnancy results at the doctors office my ex narc messaged me saying if it was positive he wouldnt pay child support and would terminate his rights. Makes me sick how they go around manipulating for sex and attention telling you they love you...and then reality hits and they cower like the lowlife snakes they are. No human feelings. Nothing lower than that. Pure evil.
God bless you
Congratulations-well written, loved reading it - thank you - much love and blessings to you and your family ❤️❤️❤️
They will only “care” about their child when they can use them as a pawn in their chess game. Some will literally trick people into pregnancy to do that. Disgusting.
@bergen.sharon 💗💗
Adorable baby ❤️
Kudos to you! All the best!

@cathy_clarinet you’ve always commented on how extreme of a case he seems and I value your input. This was the first and only pathological person I ever dated so in a sense I have nothing to compare this individual to.
@lifeafternarc I'm comparing him to my 3 Narcs and the people who write in here.  He's horrible
@lifeafternarc completely deviant
Yours was one of the worst I've heard of. You literally ran into Satan,  I swear. Be glad he abandoned you and your child.

@anf1685 they are such sickos. The individual I dated also repeatedly assured me I’d miscarry. I had to explain to him that telling a pregnant mum she’s definitely going to miscarry is abusive (obviously I didn’t realise he was a sociopath then or I’d not have wasted my time explaining).
Glad you’re happy now 💗💗
@lifeafternarc me too!!
My ex narc told me he hoped I lost the baby while pregnant, words that I’ll never forget but on the bright side, she’s the most amazing thing that has ever happened to me!! ❤️❤️

@lifeafternarc It’s not acceptable but it’s reality. As a therapist, I can also tell you that your child and you are better off. Continued abuse is far more traumatic and damaging than healing from what happened to you. I’m not at all erasing any emotion whatsoever. I lived it myself. For me, I’m glad he cannot continue to abuse me and mess with my children’s heads. I can be glad he is gone and also healing at the same time. Being happy they’re gone doesn’t erase the pain of what they did.

@hungrybecca that’s pretty much it in a nutshell: being glad they’re gone doesn’t erase the destruction they caused.
In case it’s not clear I’m fully aware that my daughter will be far better off without knowing him. This post is about highlighting some of the chaos and destruction sociopaths and narcissists cause.
@lifeafternarc Absolutely. They are horrific.

I’m so sorry you went through such terror. My ex narc husband hasn’t seen our kids for 3 years. His choice. I’ll be honest. It’s way better without him. I get feeling invalidated by people saying you’re lucky but honestly, it’s true. We are more fortunate they are not around to abuse us. I am so glad you are free of that. ❤️
@frederique_mvp very interesting comment! Thank you —- I believe many of us rapidly completely lose touch with what’s normal and acceptable once we get into a relationshit with a narc or sociopath

It's intriguing how I realized how abnormal my relationship was when I observed my best friend interact with her boyfriend a few years ago. It took me quite a while to accept that there was a problem with him (my therapist introduced the idea and I read a alot about it, but always found he was not quite as bad as described), but observing them was a real eye opener. (It still took me a lot of time afterwards to leave him, but that's another story). I think it's also the reason why they want to isolate us: after a while you don't know what is normal behaviour anymore, and you only realise it when you can compare... You have a beautiful baby and I wish you and her a wonderful and happy life...
@dinsnyggakompis So glad that my page has been helpful to you 💗
and this powerful music from the lion king!! ❤️😍take care sweetie. thanks for sharing, im 100% sure i would be in the same situation as i was last year at this time, if it wasnt for this account 🙏🏼❤️
Congratulations to your family! Welcome new baby.
@wandererie absolutely spot on. It’s shocking how rapidly narc targets end up lowering their standards and expectations without even consciously realising what is happening

So true.. living with a narc is just a continuous lowering of standards until you don't even realise why you're so sad // and that what's happening is NOT normal in any universe. Always glad to see people out there living sane, healthy, happy lives!
I’ve been through it
@heatherjmarks 💯

So good! It’s amazing how seeing other people experience normal life milestones together in a healthy way can put in perspective the disfunction we endured. I work in a hospital and frequently see spouses caring for their ill loved one, bringing flowers, milkshakes, giving hugs— all beautiful things. But things that shine a spotlight on how low I allowed the bar to fall in my own marriage. These people validate what I felt was reasonable all along and the beauty of their love inspires me to keep my standards high.
If that is your baby girl, then my God, she is so cute, I watched the video at least 10 times, because 💙💙💙 My heart melted :)
